	<term>collapse box</term>
	<definition><p>Box at the right end of a window's <glossary tag="title bar">title bar</glossary> (on <glossary tag="Mac OS">Mac OS systems</glossary>) that hides everything but the <glossary tag="title bar">title bar</glossary> when you click it. Clicking the collapse box again reveals the window contents.</p></definition>
